# Cloudflare Pages headers.
#
# COOP/COEP make the browser cross-origin isolated, which is required to expose
# SharedArrayBuffer — the zero-copy channel the transient (MOC) solver uses in
# Phase 3 to stream simulation fields from the Web Worker to the render thread.
# Setting them now keeps dev (vite server headers) and prod consistent.
#
# Because COEP is require-corp, the app must stay fully self-contained: no
# cross-origin scripts, fonts, or images. All assets are bundled locally.
/*
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: require-corp
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
